<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 06 at 3:28PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Rockbridge and southeastern Bath Counties through 400 PM EDT...
At 327 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Nimrod Hall, or near Millboro, moving southeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Goshen...
Millboro...
Nimrod Hall...
Bells Valley...
and Yost.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
